-------------------
Installing binutils
-------------------

1. Download binutils 2.32:

  $ wget http://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/binutils/binutils-2.32.tar.bz2
  $ tar -xf binutils-2.32.tar.bz2 && mv binutils-2.32 /usr/local/popcorn/src

2. Patch binutils:

  $ patch -p0 -d /usr/local/popcorn/src/binutils-2.32 < binutils-2.32.patch

3. Build & install binutils:

  $ cd /usr/local/popcorn/src/binutils-2.32
  $ mkdir build && cd build
  $ ../configure --prefix=/usr/local/popcorn \
                 --enable-gold \
                 --disable-ld \
                 --disable-libquadmath \
                 --disable-libquadmath-support \
                 --disable-libstdcxx
  $ make
  $ make install

4. You can speed the build up by enabling parallel jobs:

  $ make -j<# of parallel jobs> install

Note: you'll need bison and flex, otherwise the installation will fail.
However, since we only need gold you may be able to manually dive into
/usr/local/popcorn/src/binutils-2.32/build/gold and do a "make install" from
there to avoid this issue.

